I surround myself with generous people, because it allows me to give without expectation. When I give my time, energy or anything to generous people, I am seldom worried about being drained or "paid back" because I know the more I can do for them, the more they will do for people in their lives; which will hopefully create a cascading effect of positive vibes into the world by "paying it forward." And the world is round, and things often have a way of finding themselves back to us. Gotta watch out for the narcissists though, the energy hoarders who will do something for people someday when they have enough, the irony being that you always have enough but just in different ways.

Most awesome day yet! I've been going through a struggle lately, trying to decide if it's time to leave an activity that I've loved for the last 7 months, but due to reasons beyond my control has become increasingly negative the last 3 months, and the last three days of yoga camp have been so helpful with the transition. I'm sooo loving your videos, mantras, and random bits of humor!  What I appreciate most is how you give your students ownership in your practice. You empower me.  Instead of saying, "Do this. Do that," you give me a meaningful mantra, and let me finish it myself.  You say, "Yogi's choice here" and list options, teaching me to listen to my body and do what works. You give me enough instruction to lead me, but you let me go the rest of the way myself, in a way that is both affirming and deeply satisfying.  To sum it up:  you respect - and expect - my need to do what works for me.    I'm approaching 50 years, yet I feel like a new person.  I surround myself with youth!  I surround myself with opportunity!    Keep channeling that positive, empowering energy, Adriene.  Namaste.
